result.name: Hainan Shaoye

reviews.text: View is good, food is average, waiters response are slow

Pretty nice place for sone Hainanese Chicken with a great view. Other dishes are also pretty nice (besides chicken, we ordered some beef, egg omelette with oysters and sweet and sour pork ribs) and the prices are reasonable. Service was fine and helpful.
Love the boneless Hainan chicken + black turnip cake here. This place is consistently delicious — my favorite Singaporean/Malay restaurant in HK

The design and decoration are pretty nice and neat. This restaurant is by the terminal so it has a good view of the harbor, but If the cruise is at the terminal, the view will be totally blocked. The food was good but not the best. I had tried some better Malaysian and Singaporean food in other restaurants. But the portion was fantastic.

I I only give one star for the decoration. All the rest is poor: service awful, we are treated like S***🤬, waiters don't even smile; food is very average; price is way to high for what we have. The most disappointed thing is the service which should be correct for the price we pay for a Hainan chicken, lol! Once is enough, never again! Much better elsewhere
